      • asCidrMaskLength

        public abstract int asCidrMaskLength()
        If this IPAddress represents a valid CIDR style netmask (see isCidrMask()) returns the length of the prefix (the number of "1" bits).
        Returns:
        length of CIDR mask if this represents a valid CIDR mask
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if isCidrMask() == false

      • isUnspecified

        public abstract boolean isUnspecified()
        Returns true if the IPAddress is unspecified.

        The unspecified addresses, also known as the wildcard addresses, refer to:

        • the IPv4Address of 0.0.0.0
        • the IPv6Address of ::
        Returns:
        true if the IPAddress is unspecified, false otherwise

      • isLoopback

        public abstract boolean isLoopback()
        Returns true if the IPAddress is a loopback address.

        Loopback addresses refer to:

        • any IPv4Address within 127.0.0.0/8
        • the IPv6Address of ::1
        Returns:
        true if the IPAddress is a loopback address, false otherwise

      • isLinkLocal

        public abstract boolean isLinkLocal()
        Returns true if the IPAddress is a link local address.

        Link local addresses refer to:

        • any IPv4Address within 169.254.0.0/16
        • any IPv6Address within fe80::/10
        Returns:
        true if the IPAddress is a link local address, false otherwise

      • withMaskOfLength

        @Nonnull
public abstract IPAddressWithMask<F> withMaskOfLength(int cidrMaskLength)
        Returns an IPAddressWithMask<F> object that represents this IP address masked by the CIDR subnet mask of the given prefix length.
        Parameters:
        cidrMaskLength - the prefix length of the CIDR subnet mask (i.e. the number of leading one-bits), where 0 <= cidrMaskLength <= (F.getLength() * 8)
        Returns:
        an IPAddressWithMask<F> object that represents this IP address masked by the CIDR subnet mask of the given prefix length
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the given prefix length was invalid
        See Also:
        IPv4Address.ofCidrMaskLength(int), IPv6Address.ofCidrMaskLength(int)

      • getBytes

        public abstract byte[] getBytes()
        Returns the raw IP address of this IPAddress object. The result is in network byte order: the highest order byte of the address is in getBytes()[0].

        Similar to InetAddress.getAddress()

        Returns:
        the raw IP address of this object
